<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 2:40PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central
Phillips County through 345 PM MDT...
At 240 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southwest of Turner, or 32 miles east of Chinook, moving
southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Malta, Dodson, Loring, Chapman and Wagner.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
